## Monthly income target

Income in retirement comes from multiple sources starting at different times:

- Pension(s) — one or more depending on career history
- Social Security (delayed during gap years — covered by cash reserve or taxable accounts in the interim)
- Portfolio withdrawals for the remainder

**During gap years:** The Social Security portion comes from HYSA or taxable accounts. The goal is to keep income low to maximize Roth conversion room.

The interactive version of this guide includes adjustable sliders so the user can model their own pension amounts and see the required portfolio withdrawal update in real time, privately.

