## The 3-bucket withdrawal strategy

Withdraw in this order: **Taxable first → Tax-deferred second → Tax-free last**

### Bucket 1 — Taxable accounts (brokerage)
- Funded with after-tax dollars
- Dividends and gains taxable each year
- Assets held over 1 year taxed at lower capital gains rates
- Use first to give other buckets more time to compound

### Bucket 2 — Tax-deferred (401k, IRA, 403b)
- Every dollar out taxed as ordinary income (higher than capital gains)
- Subject to RMDs starting at age 73
- Use strategic Roth conversions during low-income gap years to reduce future RMD exposure

### Bucket 3 — Tax-free (Roth IRA, Roth 401k, HSA)
- No tax on growth, dividends, or withdrawals
- No RMDs on Roth IRAs
- The longer it sits untouched, the more powerful it becomes
- Only spend when other buckets are exhausted

